0–1551","1444–1495":"1444–1495","–1506":"–1506","9 July 1554":"9 July 1554","25 September 1510":"25 September 1510","1495":"1495","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1444":"1444","1510":"1510","1554":"1554","1564":"1564","3 February 1506":"3 February 1506","1474":"1474","1551":"1551","1508":"1508","about 1474":"about 1474","3 February 1495":"3 February 1495","1506":"1506","25 December 1551":"25 December 1551","1549":"1549","Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, England":"Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, England","England":"England","Little Eversden, Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, England","Oakington, Cambridgeshire, England":"Oakington, Cambridgeshire, England","Huntington, Huntingtonshire, England":"Huntingdon, Huntingdonshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Leete","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Leet  .","History: An early American bearer of this name was one of the founders ofGuilford, CT. William Leete (<i>c.</i> 1613–83), a colonial governorof New Haven colony and CT, was born at Dodington, Huntingtonshire,England. He converted to Puritanism and sailed for America to escapepersecution in May 1639."],"variants":[{"name":"Leet","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone who lived by a watercourse orroad junction, Old English <i>gelǣt</i>, or a habitational namefrom Leat in Devon, or The Leete in Essex, named with this element."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":75,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Leete was born about 1474, in Ipswich, Suffolk, England as the son of Thomas Leete and Alse Huntington. He married Maria Slade in 1500, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 9 July 1554, in Oakington, Cambridgeshire, England, at the age of 81, and was buried in Oakington, Cambridgeshire, England."},"et":{"about 1474–9 July 1554":"umbes 1474–9. juuli 1554","1474–1554":"1474–1554","1508–1564":"1508–1564","1478–1510":"1478–1510","1500–1551":"1500–1551","1444–1495":"1444–1495","–1506":"–1506","9 July 1554":"9. juuli 1554","25 September 1510":"25. september 1510","1495":"1495","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1444":"1444","1510":"1510","1554":"1554","1564":"1564","3 February 1506":"3. veebruar 1506","1474":"1474","1551":"1551","1508":"1508","about 1474":"umbes 1474","3 February 1495":"3. veebruar 1495","1506":"1506","25 December 1551":"25. detsember 1551","1549":"1549","Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, England":"Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, England","England":"England","Little Eversden, Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, England","Oakington, Cambridgeshire, England":"Oakington, Cambridgeshire, England","Huntington, Huntingtonshire, England":"Huntingdon, Huntingdonshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1474–9 July 1554":"noin 1474–9. heinäkuuta 1554","1474–1554":"1474–1554","1508–1564":"1508–1564","1478–1510